result.execSummary:
The defendant Jacob D. Smith was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Child Enticement-Sexual Contact, a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.07(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: No contact with minors unless supervised by an agent approved adult 25 years or older. Contact includes direct personal or physical and indirect contact by phone, in writing of any kind, entry to the person's residence or place of employment together with contact through other persons. Access to internet ONLY with the approval of the agent/treatment team. No use of internet and computer other than for searching and applying for employment, including applying for unemployment benefits, so as long as an adult (approved by agent) is present and monitoring his computer and internet use for these purposes ONLY-at agent's/treatment team discretion.

Comply with Sex Offender registry. Anger Management, Parenting classes, and/or financial management class at agent's discretion. Treatment as directed by agent; successfully complete an individualized sex offender treatment program.

May transfer to Wood Co. for Jail and/or Probation.

If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.  

A copy of the police report has been electronically sent to the probation office.
